      • buildWithHandler

        public <T> T buildWithHandler(java.lang.Class<? extends SpecHandler<T>> specClass,
                     com.typesafe.config.Config config)
                   throws SpecificationException

        Configure an object using a specification and a particular spec handler.

        Parameters:
        specClass - The specification handler interface, defining the kind of object to configure. If it is a concrete instantiable class, then the class is used directly; otherwise, it is looked up using the service provider interface and the implementations are searched for one that handles the type specified in the type key in the config.
        config - A Typesafe configuration for the object.
        T - The object type.
        Returns:
        A configured object.
        Throws:
        SpecificationException

      • build

        public <T> T build(java.lang.Class<T> type,
          com.typesafe.config.Config config)
        throws SpecificationException

        Configure an object using a specification.

        Parameters:
        type - The type of object to build. The class must be annotated with SpecHandlerInterface to specify a spec handler, or have a public static method fromSpec that takes a specification and a Config and creates an object.
        config - A Typesafe configuration for the object.
        T - The object type.
        Returns:
        A configured object.
        Throws:
        SpecificationException
